# Kyber-Zip relay — Caddy v2 reverse proxy with automatic HTTPS.
#
# Replace relay.example.com with your domain (an A record must point it at the
# droplet's IP). Caddy provisions and renews a Let's Encrypt certificate
# automatically, so the client can use https://relay.example.com.
#
# Caddy v2 streams request/response bodies and imposes no upload size limit by
# default, so large .kyz uploads pass straight through; the relay itself caps
# size via RELAY_MAX_BYTES. No timeout tuning is needed for big transfers.

relay.example.com {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
}
